{"name": "cvectors", "metadata": {"name": "cvectors", "version": "9.1.2", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "License :: OSI Approved :: GNU General Public License v3 or later (GPLv3+)", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "A simple complex vector package.", "upload_time": 1734558676}, "documentation": ["# Cvectors\n\nCvectors is a Python package for 2D vectors. It provides a class,\n`Vector`, which uses `complex` internally.\n\nUsage is as follows:\n\n```python\n>>> from cvectors import Vector\n>>> foo = Vector(4, 3)\n>>> foo\nVector(4.0, 3.0)\n>>> foo.x\n4.0\n>>> foo.y\n3.0\n>>> foo.r\n5.0\n>>> bar = Vector(4, 5)\n>>> foo + bar\nVector(8.0, 8.0)\n>>> foo.dot(bar)\n31.0\n>>> import math\n>>> foo.rotate(math.pi / 2)\nVector(-2.9999999999999996, 4.0)\n>>> Vector.from_polar(r=3, theta=5) - Vector.from_polar(r=5, theta=2)\nVector(2.9317207391253906, -7.423259958117824)\n>>> Vector(5, 6).perp_dot(Vector(-6, 1))\n41.0\n>>> abs(foo)\n5.0\n>>> Vector(1, -9).rec()\n(1.0, -9.0)\n>>> Vector(1, -9).pol()\n(9.055385138137417, -1.460139105621001)\n>>> Vector(3, 2).perp()\nVector(-2.0, 3.0)\n>>> Vector(3.142, 2.718).round()\n(3, 3)\n>>> Vector(3.142, 2.718).round(1)\n(3.1, 2.7)\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "cvectors", "documentation": ["A package for using complex numbers as 2D vectors."], "functions": [{"name": "cvectors._from_complex", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "z", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "_object_setattr", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "_vector", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "_vector_new", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "cvectors._object_setattr", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "cvectors.Vector", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "cvectors.Vector.__init__", "async